# i18n & RTL Governance — Bunyan

## Language Config

- Primary: Arabic (ar) — RTL
- Secondary: English (en) — LTR
- Default locale: ar

## Translation Keys

- Dot notation with category prefix: `projects.status.active`
- Snake_case keys: `validation.field_required`
- Never hardcode Arabic/English text in templates
- Always provide both ar + en translations
- Use parameters for dynamic values: `:amount`

## Backend Translation Structure

```
backend/resources/lang/
├── ar/ (auth.php, validation.php, projects.php, orders.php, common.php)
└── en/ (same files)
```

## Frontend Translation Structure

```
frontend/locales/
├── ar.json
└── en.json
```

## RTL Layout Rules

- `dir="rtl"` as default on `<html>`
- Use CSS logical properties:
  - `margin-inline-start` / `margin-inline-end`
  - `padding-inline-start` / `padding-inline-end`
  - `border-inline-start` / `border-inline-end`
- Nuxt UI handles RTL natively

## Currency & Formatting

- Currency: Saudi Riyal (SAR / ر.س)
- Date: `Intl.DateTimeFormat('ar-SA')`
- Numbers: Arabic-Hindi numerals optional (٠١٢٣٤٥٦٧٨٩)

## Validation Messages (Arabic)

All validation errors MUST have Arabic translations:

```php
'name.required' => 'حقل الاسم مطلوب',
'email.email' => 'البريد الإلكتروني غير صالح',
```
